1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. Nf3 cxd4 4. Nxd4 e5 5. Nb5 d5 6. cxd5 Bc5 7. N5c3 O-O 8. g3 Qb6 9. e3 Bf5 10. Bg2 Nbd7 11. O-O e4 12. b3 $5 ({The standard continuation} 12. Nd2 {is also good, for example:} Rfe8 13. Qa4 Qb4 14. Qxb4 Bxb4 15. Nb5 Rec8 16. a3 Bf8 17. Nc3 Re8 18. h3 h6 19. b4 Nb6 20. Bb2 Nbxd5 21. Nxd5 Nxd5 22. g4 Bg6 23. Nc4 Rac8 24. Rac1 Nb6 25. Na5 Na4 26. Bd4 $16 b6 27. Nc6 a5 28. Rfd1 axb4 29. axb4 Nc5 30. Ne5 $18 Nb3 31. Rxc8 Rxc8 32. Bxb6 Bh7 33. b5 f6 34. Nc6 Bg6 35. Rd8 Rxd8 36. Nxd8 Bd6 37. Ba7 Bc5 38. Bxc5 Nxc5 39. b6 Nd7 40. b7 Nb8 41. Kh2 Kf8 42. Ne6+ Ke7 43. Nxg7 Kd6 44. h4 Ke5 45. Kg3) (12. Na4 $2 Qd6 13. Nxc5 Nxc5 14. Nc3 Nd3 $17) 12... Rfe8 ({One important idea behind 12.b3 becomes apparent after} 12... Ne5 $2 {Black would very much like to be able to play this move...} 13. Na4 Qd6 14. Nxc5 Qxc5 15. Ba3 $18) 13. Bb2 Rac8 ({This time,} 13... Ne5 {is far less easily refuted:} 14. Na4 Qd6 15. Nd2 $1 {, and now} Nd3 {fails due to} 16. Bxf6 Qxf6 17. Nxe4 Rxe4 18. Qxd3 Rxa4 19. Qb5 $18) 14. Nd2 Bf8 15. h3 h6 16. Ne2 Qd8 17. Rc1 $14 1-0

