1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. Nf3 cxd4 4. Nxd4 e5 5. Nb5 d5 6. cxd5 Bc5 7. N5c3 O-O 8. g3 Qb6 9. e3 Bg4 10. Be2 Bxe2 11. Qxe2 e4 12. a3 (12. Nd2 $6 Bb4) 12... Re8 13. Nd2 $6 (13. b4 $1 {was better and much easier, for example} Bf8 14. Nd2 Nbd7 15. O-O Qd6 16. Bb2 Nb6 (16... Ne5 17. Ndxe4 Nxe4 18. Nxe4 Qxd5 19. Bxe5 $16) 17. Rac1 Nbxd5 18. Nxd5 Nxd5 19. Rfd1 $16) 13... Qc7 {Preventing b2-b4 for the moment and delaying the development of White's remaining pieces.} 14. O-O a6 15. Rd1 Nbd7 16. b4 $1 {White finds a tactical solution to his problems. Now the game becomes very sharp and concrete.} (16. Nb3 $2 Ne5 $36) 16... Bd4 (16... Bxb4 {clearly favours White:} 17. Ncxe4 Nxe4 18. Nxe4 Rxe4 19. axb4 Rxb4 20. Bb2 $1 $16 ({But not} 20. e4 $2 Qe5 $15)) 17. Bb2 Bxc3 18. Rac1 Nxd5 19. Nxe4 Rxe4 20. Rxd5 Rc4 ({No better is} 20... Nb6 21. Rc5) 21. Rxc3 Rxc3 22. Bxc3 Qxc3 23. Rxd7 Qxa3 24. Qc4 $18 {The fog has cleared and White ends up with an extra pawn and the far more active rook.} (24. Rxb7 $2 {would have allowed Black to force a theoretically drawn rook ending:} Qc1+ 25. Kg2 Qc6+ 26. Qf3 Qxf3+ 27. Kxf3 h5 28. h3 a5 29. bxa5 Rxa5 30. Rb8+ Kh7 31. Rb7 Kg8 32. Rc7 g6 33. g4 hxg4+ 34. hxg4 Kg7 35. Kg3 Ra2 36. f4 Re2 37. Kf3 Re1 38. Re7 Rb1 39. e4 Re1 40. e5 Kf8 41. Rb7 Kg7 42. Kg3 Kf8 43. Kh4 Kg7 44. Kg5 Re2 45. Re7 Re1 46. f5 Rxe5 $11) 24... Qa1+ 25. Kg2 Qf6 26. Rxb7 g6 27. Qc5 $1 Qe6 28. Re7 Qb3 29. h4 h5 (29... Qa2 30. h5 Qb1 31. h6 $18) (29... Rb8 30. h5 Qxb4 (30... Rxb4 31. Re8+) 31. Re8+ Kg7 32. Qe5+ $18) 30. e4 Rb8 31. Qd6 Rxb4 (31... Ra8 32. e5 Qc2 33. Qf6 $18 (33. e6 Qe4+ 34. Kh2 fxe6 35. Rxe6 $18) 33... Qe4+ 34. Kh2 Rf8 35. e6 $18) 32. Re8+ Kg7 (32... Kh7 33. Qf6 Qb2 34. Rh8#) 33. Qf8+ Kf6 34. Qh8# 1-0

