{[%evp 0,31,13,17,54,54,39,26,26,22,88,31,33,30,27,27,27,27,27,26,35,22,21,27,29,41,79,46,40,39,46,16,23,42]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6 5. c4 Bg7 (5... Nf6 $5 6. Nc3 Nxd4 7. Qxd4 (7. e5 $5 Ne4 $3 $132) 7... d6 8. f3 Bg7 9. Be3 $1 (9. Bg5 O-O (9... h6 10. Be3) 10. Qd2 Be6 11. Rc1 a6 12. b3 Rc8 (12... Qa5 $2 13. Nd5 $1 Qxd2+ 14. Kxd2 Bxd5 (14... Nxd5 $2 15. cxd5 Bd7 16. Rc7 $18 (16. Bxe7 $2 Bh6+)) 15. cxd5 Rac8 16. Rxc8 $3 (16. Be2 $16) 16... Rxc8 17. g3 $3 $18 Kf8 (17... e6 18. Bh3 $1 (18. dxe6 $6 fxe6 19. Bh3 Kf7) 18... Re8 19. dxe6 fxe6 20. Rc1 $18) 18. Bh3 Rc7 19. Rc1 Rxc1 20. Kxc1 Ke8 21. Bc8 $18) 13. Be2 $1 (13. Bd3 $5 b5 14. cxb5 axb5 15. O-O) 13... Qa5 (13... b5 $1 14. cxb5 axb5 15. O-O b4 16. Nb5 Qa5 17. Be3 Rxc1 18. Rxc1 Ra8 19. Rc2 $14) 14. Na4 $1 (14. Nd5 Qxd2+ 15. Kxd2 Nxd5 16. cxd5 Bd7 17. Rxc8 Rxc8 18. Rc1 Rxc1 19. Kxc1 $11 {The endgame is objectively a draw, but due to his space advantage, White has some practical chances to play for a win.}) 14... Qxd2+ 15. Kxd2 h6 16. Be3 Nd7 17. Nc3 $1 Nf6 (17... f5 18. exf5) (17... Rfe8 18. Nd5) 18. g4 Rfe8 19. h4 Nd7 20. Nd5 Bxd5 21. cxd5 Bb2 22. Rxc8 Rxc8 23. Rb1 Bc3+ (23... Ba3 24. b4 a5 25. bxa5) 24. Kd1 $16) 9... O-O 10. Qd2 Be6 (10... Bd7 11. Rc1 a6 12. b3 Rc8 13. Be2 Bc6 14. O-O Nd7 15. Rfd1 f5 16. exf5 Rxf5 17. Bd4 $16) 11. Rc1 Qa5 (11... a6 12. b3 Rc8 13. Be2 Qa5 (13... Nd7 $6 14. O-O Re8 15. Nd5 $16 Bxd5 16. cxd5 $16) 14. Na4 $5 (14. O-O $1 b5 $2 15. cxb5 axb5 16. Nd5 $18 (16. Nxb5 $18) 16... Qxd2 17. Nxe7+) 14... Qxd2+ 15. Kxd2 Nd7 16. Nc3 $1 $14) 12. b3 Rfc8 {This move is a prophylactic against Nd5. Additionally, Black is planning to proceed with ...a7-a6 followed by ...b7-b5.} ({The immediate} 12... a6 {is answered with} 13. Nd5 Qxd2+ 14. Kxd2 Bxd5 15. cxd5 Rac8 16. Rxc8 Rxc8 17. g3 $3 $18 {[%cal Gf1h3] with Bh3 to follow. After taking the c-file under control, White will be winning.}) 13. Be2 a6 14. Na4 {The most precise way of forcing an endgame.} ({In case of} 14. Nd5 $6 {Black achieves equality with} Qxd2+ 15. Kxd2 Nxd5 16. cxd5 Bd7 {[%cal Gg7b2] with ...Bb2 to follow. White cannot take the control of the c-file.}) 14... Qxd2+ 15. Kxd2 Nd7 16. g4 {Gaining space on the kingside is White's most typical idea in this endgame.} Rcb8 $5 {This fashionable move is connected with an interesting positional pawn sacrifice.} ({As I have pointed out in the lecture, the move} 16... f5 {should be met with} 17. exf5 gxf5 18. h3 {when the kingside tension is definitely in White's favour. A possible idea would be f3-f4 followed by Bf3.}) 17. Nc3 b5 18. Nd5 Bxd5 19. cxd5 Nc5 $1 {[%cal Gg7b2,Gb2a3,Ga6a5];½-½ Aronian,L (2767)-Duda,J (2757) Norway Chess 8th 2020 (8) This is the point. Black is now planning to follow with the maneuver ...Bb2-a3.} {In my opinion, the most precise move would be} 20. Rc2 $14 {when it's not clear how Black can create counterplay.}) (5... Bh6 $6 {This move was played a few times by Tiviakov. There is some logic behind exchanging the dark-squared bishop, but modern computer analysis buried it.} 6. Bxh6 Nxh6 7. Nc3 $16) 6. Be3 Nf6 7. Nc3 d6 (7... Ng4 8. Qxg4 Nxd4 (8... Bxd4 $2 9. Bxd4 Nxd4 10. O-O-O $3 e5 11. Qg3 f6 12. f4 d6 13. f5 $16 gxf5 $4 14. Qg7 Rf8 15. Nd5 Rf7 16. Qg8+ Rf8 17. Qxh7 Rf7 18. Qg8+ Rf8 19. Qg6+ Rf7 20. Rxd4 exd4 21. exf5 Kf8 22. Be2 $18) 9. Qd1 Nc6 (9... Ne6 10. Rc1 Qa5 11. Qd2 $1 (11. Qd5) (11. f3 $16) (11. f4 $16) 11... O-O 12. b3 d6 13. Be2 Nc5 14. f3 f5 15. exf5 $14) (9... e5 $5 10. Bd3 O-O 11. O-O d6 12. b3 (12. Nb5 $5) 12... Be6 13. Qd2 a6 14. Rac1 Rc8 15. Rfd1 $16 (15. Ne2 $16)) 10. Qd2 $1 (10. Be2 $2 Bxc3+ $1 $132) 10... O-O 11. Be2 (11. Rc1) 11... d6 12. Rc1 Qa5 (12... f5 $2 13. exf5 Bxf5 14. O-O $16) 13. b3 Bd7 14. O-O $1 Rac8 15. Rfd1 Rfe8 16. h3 $16 a6 17. Na4 $16) 8. Be2 O-O 9. O-O Bd7 (9... Nxd4 10. Bxd4 Bd7 11. h3) (9... a6 $5 10. h3 $1 Nxd4 11. Bxd4 Bd7 (11... Be6 12. Rc1 (12. Qd2 Qa5 13. Rac1 $4 Nxe4) 12... Qa5 13. b3 Rfc8 14. Qd3 Nd7 15. Bxg7 Kxg7 16. f4) 12. a4 $5 $14 (12. Qc2 $1 Bc6 13. Rfd1 (13. b4 $16) 13... Nd7 14. Bxg7 Kxg7 15. Bg4 $16 Ne5 16. c5 Nxg4 17. hxg4 $16)) (9... Qa5 $6 10. Nb3 $1 Qd8 11. Rc1 Be6 12. f3 Rc8 13. Qd2 Ne5 14. Nd5 Bxd5 15. cxd5 a6 16. Rxc8 Qxc8 17. Rc1 Qb8 18. Nd4 $16) (9... a5 $2 10. Ndb5 $16) 10. h3 Nxd4 (10... a5 $2 11. Ndb5 $16 Ne5 12. Rc1 Rc8 (12... Bxb5 13. cxb5) 13. b3 $16) (10... Rc8 11. Nf3 $14 (11. Rc1 Nxd4 12. Bxd4 Bc6 13. Qc2 Nd7 14. Bxg7 Kxg7 15. Rfd1 $14)) 11. Bxd4 Bc6 12. Qc2 $1 a5 (12... Nd7 13. Bxg7 Kxg7 14. Rad1 a6 15. Bg4 Ne5 (15... Rc8 16. b3 h5 17. Bxd7 Qxd7 18. e5) 16. c5 Nxg4 17. hxg4 Qd7 18. cxd6 exd6 19. f3 Rad8 20. Qf2 $16) (12... Rc8 $6 13. Rad1 Nd7 14. Bxg7 Kxg7 15. Bg4 $1 h5 16. Bxd7 Bxd7 17. b3 $16 f6 18. a4) 13. Rad1 $3 Nd7 (13... a4 14. c5 $1 $16) 14. Bxg7 Kxg7 15. Bg4 $3 Nc5 (15... Ne5 16. c5 $16 Nxg4 17. hxg4 Qc8 18. cxd6 exd6 19. f3 Qe6 20. Rd4 $18 (20. Qf2 $18)) 16. e5 $16 *

