{This is a solution for players who like to avoid the theory after 3.d4 and transpose into the anti-King's Indian setup recommended in later parts of this repertoire. With 3.b3, White intends a double-fianchetto followed by a quiet, positional game. A typical characteristic of these positions is that Black can easily overextend his position and create weaknesses that White will exploit - and this happens surprisingly often. Unfortunately, Black has one narrow path to reach a very satisfactory position, but this requires him to find (unlikely) or rather know the best 3rd, 4th, 5th, and 7th move.} 1. Nf3 Nf6 ({After} 1... c5 2. c4 Nc6 3. b3 e5 4. Bb2 e4 (4... d6 5. g3) 5. Ng1 $1 {is surprisingly good for White. White's loss of time due to moving his knight back to g1 is easily balanced by Black's numerous pawn moves, that not only cost time but also created weaknesses and overextended his position.} Nf6 6. Bxf6 $1 Qxf6 7. Nc3 Qe5 8. g3 g6 9. e3 Bg7 10. Bg2 f5 11. Nge2 O-O 12. O-O d6 13. d3 $16) 2. c4 c5 (2... g6 {When playing this variation, it is always important to answer a fianchetto with a counter-fianchetto before this becomes problematic due to the opposite bishop's presence on the diagonal.} 3. b3 Bg7 4. Bb2 O-O 5. g3 d6 6. Bg2 c5) 3. b3 $5 Nc6 $1 (3... g6 4. Bb2 Bg7 5. g3 O-O (5... b6 6. Bg2 Bb7) 6. Bg2) (3... b6 4. g3 $1 (4. Bb2 $6 {gives Black the interesting option} Bb7 5. g3 Bxf3) 4... Bb7 5. Bg2 g6 6. Bb2 Bg7 7. O-O O-O) 4. Bb2 e6 $1 (4... g6 5. g3) (4... d5 $5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. Nc3 Nxc3 7. Bxc3 f6 8. e3 e5 9. Bc4) (4... d6 5. g3 e5 6. d3 g6 7. Bg2 Bg7 8. O-O O-O 9. Nc3) 5. g3 (5. e3 d5 6. cxd5 exd5 7. Bb5) 5... d5 6. cxd5 exd5 7. Bg2 (7. d4 $2 {Unfortunately, this cannot be played with a queenside fianchetto and the king in the centre due to} cxd4 8. Nxd4 Bb4+) 7... d4 $1 {This is the sequence of moves that Black has to play in order to exploit the problems of the 3.b3 move-order. The resulting position is fully playable for White, but he has no claim for an opening advantage.} (7... Be7 8. O-O O-O 9. d4) 8. O-O Be7 9. Na3 O-O 10. e3 $132 *

