1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 {Our move order is 2.c4} b6 3. Bg2 Bb7 4. c4 c5 5. b3 g6 6. Bb2 Bg7 7. O-O O-O 8. d4 {In this symmetrical position after all bishops are fianchettoed and both players castle, White has 2 good moves - d4 and Nc3} (8. Nc3 $5) 8... cxd4 (8... Nc6 $6 9. d5 $1 Na5 10. Nbd2 {[%csl Ra5] The knight on a5 is misplaced} d6 11. e4 e5 12. Ne1 {[%cal Ge1d3,Gf2f4]} Nd7 13. Nd3 f5 14. f4 $1 {In this position which is about to open up, Black has 2 inactive pieces - the Bb7 and Na5. The bishop from b7 can potentially join the game at some point with Bc8, but for the knight that would be more difficult. Any complications in the center should favor White because of the better-placed pieces.} exf4 15. Bxg7 Kxg7 16. Nxf4 $18 {[%csl Ge6]}) 9. Qxd4 (9. Nxd4 {Is not very good, after Bxg2 our king will be exposed, and there is a possibility that our knight will be pinned on the a1-h8 diagonal} Bxg2 10. Kxg2 d5 $1 {Now it's Black who has the better side of equality}) 9... d6 (9... Ne8 10. Qd2 Bxb2 (10... d6 11. Bxg7 Nxg7 12. Nc3 Nd7 13. Nd5 {Next the rooks will be developed. I would also like to provoke e6 which would make the d6 pawn very weak} (13. Rfd1 $5 {[%cal Ga1c1,Gc3d5]}) 13... Bxd5 14. cxd5 {[%csl Gc6][%cal Gf3d4,Gd4c6] Now we have the c6 square as an outpost} Nf5 {Black prevents our Nd4-Nc6 plan, so first we should consider playing either e4 or even g4 to kick the knight away, and then jump Nd4-Nc6} 15. e4 $1 $16 {[%cal Gf3d4,Gd4c6]}) 11. Qxb2 Nc6 12. Nc3 d6 13. Rfd1 {[%cal Ga1c1,Gc3d5]} (13. Rad1 {With a possibility of e4 and Rfe1}) 13... Nc7 14. Nd5 Nxd5 15. cxd5 $16 {With Nd4-Nc6 next}) 10. Nc3 Ne4 11. Qe3 Nxc3 12. Bxc3 $14 Nd7 13. Bxg7 Kxg7 14. Rad1 Rc8 15. h4 Nf6 16. Qd4 Qc7 17. Bh3 Rcd8 18. Rc1 Qc5 19. Qb2 Kg8 20. Nd4 Qe5 21. Bg2 Bxg2 22. Kxg2 Rc8 23. Rfd1 Rfd8 24. b4 d5 25. c5 bxc5 26. bxc5 Ne4 27. c6 Qf6 28. e3 Rd6 29. f3 Nxg3 30. Kxg3 Qe5+ 31. Kg2 Rdxc6 32. Rxc6 Rxc6 33. Rc1 Rxc1 34. Qxc1 Kg7 35. Nc6 Qf6 36. Qc5 Qxh4 37. Qxe7 Qh5 38. Ne5 Qf5 39. Nd7 h5 40. Qe5+ Qxe5 41. Nxe5 Kf6 42. Nc6 a6 43. Nb4 Ke5 44. Nxa6 d4 45. exd4+ Kxd4 46. a4 Kc4 47. Nb8 Kb4 48. Nc6+ Kxa4 49. Ne5 f6 50. Nxg6 Kb5 51. Nf4 Kc5 52. Nxh5 f5 53. Ng7 f4 54. Ne6+ Kd5 55. Nxf4+ Ke5 56. Kg3 Kf5 57. Nd3 Kg5 58. f4+ Kf5 59. Kf3 1-0

