1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. g3 g6 4. b3 {Preparing to fianchetto the Bc1 against the bishop on g7} b6 5. Bg2 Bb7 6. O-O Bg7 7. Bb2 O-O 8. d4 cxd4 (8... Nc6 $2 9. d5) (8... d6 9. d5 {[%cal Gb1c3] With a big space advantage}) (8... d5 9. dxc5 bxc5 $6 {Black will be left with a weak isolated pawn on c5} (9... dxc4 10. cxb6 $14) 10. cxd5 Nxd5 11. Bxg7 {We want to expose Black's king so we capture on g7} Kxg7 12. Qc1 Nd7 13. Nc3 {[%cal Gf1d1,Gd1d8]} (13. Qb2+ {I wouldn't like to spend this check for no reason}) 13... Nxc3 14. Qxc3+ Kg8 15. Rfd1 $16) 9. Qxd4 Nc6 10. Qc3 $1 {[%cal Gf1d1,Gc3e1,Gb1c3] Aronian's idea!} Rc8 (10... Nh5 11. Qc1 {Qc2 may be possible but we can simply avoid unnecessary Nb4 ideas} Bxb2 12. Qxb2 d6 13. Nc3 Nf6 14. Nd5 $14) 11. Rd1 Qc7 12. Qe1 $1 {The knight is coming to c3 and everything is protected. Additionally, the queen from e1 can help support the e4 advance later} Qb8 13. Nc3 Rfd8 14. Rac1 e6 (14... d6 15. e4 $14 (15. Bh3 $5 {Provoking weaknesses} e6 {White may already consider moves like Nb5 or e4} 16. Nb5 (16. e4 $2 {Is a move we would like to play but unfortunately it fails tactically:} Nxe4 $1 {[%csl Rb2][%cal Gg7b2]} 17. Qxe4 Ne5 $19 {[%csl Re4,Rf3][%cal Gb7f3,Ge5f3]})) (15. Nd5 $6 Nxd5 16. Bxg7 {Intending cxd5 and Nd4, but Black has} Ne3 $1)) (14... Ne4 {White will either improve the position with e3 or solve the pin issue with} 15. Ba1 Nxc3 16. Bxc3 Bxc3 17. Qxc3 d6 18. Qe3 {[%csl Ge3][%cal Ge3e7,Ge3h6,Gf3g5] Puts pressure on e7 but the main idea is Qh6 and Ng5. Such attacks are justified because Black has weaknesses in the pawn structure in front of the king on g8 and also, all Black's pieces are on the queenside.}) 15. Ng5 h6 16. Nge4 Nxe4 17. Bxe4 Ne7 18. Ba3 Nf5 19. Bxf5 gxf5 20. Be7 Re8 21. Bd6 Qa8 22. Nb5 Ba6 23. Nc7 Rxc7 24. Bxc7 Qc6 25. Bd6 Bb7 26. f3 e5 27. Qd2 e4 28. Qd5 Qc8 29. Qxf5 exf3 30. exf3 Re2 31. Qd3 Qe8 32. Bf4 Qe7 33. Rf1 Qc5+ 34. Kh1 Rxa2 35. Rce1 Qh5 36. Re2 Rxe2 37. Qxe2 Bc6 38. Kg2 b5 39. cxb5 Bxb5 40. Qe8+ Kh7 41. Rc1 Qd5 42. Qe4+ Qxe4 43. fxe4 Bc6 44. Rc4 Kg6 45. g4 h5 46. g5 a6 47. Kf3 f6 48. gxf6 Bxf6 49. Rc2 Kf7 50. Ke3 Bd8 51. Kd4 Ke6 52. Rg2 Bf6+ 53. Kd3 d5 54. e5 Bb5+ 55. Kc3 Bh4 56. Rg7 Bf2 57. Rg5 h4 58. Kd2 Bc5 59. Rg6+ Kf5 60. Rf6+ Ke4 61. e6 d4 62. Bh6 Be7 63. Rf7 Bb4+ 64. Kd1 Ke5 65. e7 Ke6 66. Rf4 Bxe7 67. Rxd4 Bf6 68. Rd2 Be5 69. Rf2 Bc6 70. Bf4 Bd4 71. Rd2 Bc5 72. Rc2 Kd5 73. Ke2 Bd7 74. Rd2+ Kc6 75. Kf3 Be6 76. Rd3 Kb5 77. Ke4 h3 78. Ke5 Bg4 79. Rg3 Bd7 80. Be3 Ba3 81. Bd2 Bc5 82. Rg5 Kc6 83. Rg6+ Kb5 84. Rh6 Bb6 85. Kd6 Bg4 86. Rh4 Bc5+ 87. Kc7 Be6 88. Rh5 1-0

