1. c4 c5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. b3 b6 4. Bb2 {Going Bb2 and not g3 in this position, gives Black the extra option Bb7 g3 Bxf3. It's an interesting possibility, White shouldn't be afraid of it but there is no reason to allow it, White can simply start with 4.g3} Bb7 5. g3 (5. e3 {In case you play Bb2 fast or make a mistake, in my opinion now e3 may be better}) 5... g6 (5... Bxf3 6. exf3 Nc6 {Is an interesting possibility for Black}) 6. Bg2 Bg7 7. O-O O-O 8. d4 cxd4 9. Qxd4 Nc6 10. Qc3 {[%cal Gf1d1,Gc3e1,Gb1c3]} Qc7 11. Rd1 Rad8 12. Qe1 d5 13. cxd5 Rxd5 14. Nc3 (14. Rxd5 $5 {This is better as we would trade on g7 and expose the king a bit} Nxd5 15. Bxg7 Kxg7 16. Nc3 Nxc3 $6 17. Qxc3+ $14 {And next White wants to play moves like Rc1 or Nd4}) 14... Rxd1 15. Nxd1 Rd8 16. Rc1 Bh6 17. e3 Qd7 18. Bxf6 exf6 19. Nb2 Bg7 20. Rd1 Qe7 21. Rxd8+ Nxd8 22. Nc4 f5 23. Qd2 Ne6 24. Nfe5 Bxg2 25. Kxg2 Qb7+ 26. Kg1 Qe4 27. Nxf7 Qb1+ 28. Kg2 f4 29. exf4 Nd4 30. Nfe5 Qe4+ 31. f3 Qd5 32. Ne3 Qc5 33. b4 Qd6 34. Nc2 Nf5 35. Qxd6 Nxd6 36. Kf2 Nb5 37. Ke3 Kf8 38. Kd3 Ke8 39. a4 Nc7 40. Ne3 a6 41. Kc4 Bf8 42. b5 axb5+ 43. axb5 Bc5 44. Nd5 Ne6 45. Nf6+ Kf8 46. Nxh7+ Kg7 47. Ng5 Nc7 48. Ne4 Bg1 49. h4 Ne6 50. Nc6 Nc7 51. Ne7 Ne6 52. f5 Nd4 53. fxg6 Nxf3 54. h5 Nd4 55. g4 Ne6 56. Nf5+ Kh8 1-0

