1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 g6 3. b3 Bg7 4. Bb2 b6 5. Bg2 Bb7 6. O-O O-O 7. c4 c5 8. d4 cxd4 9. Qxd4 Nc6 10. Qc3 Rc8 11. Rd1 Na5 12. Qe1 d6 13. Nc3 {We are not threatening to play e4 yet as Black will take it, but we simply want to continue developing, for example Rac1} Ne4 14. Rac1 Nxc3 15. Bxc3 $14 Bxc3 16. Rxc3 Qc7 17. Re3 Rfd8 18. Bh3 Rb8 19. Nd4 a6 20. Ne6 $3 Qc6 (20... fxe6 21. Bxe6+ $18 {[%cal Ge1c3]} Kf8 (21... Kg7 22. Qc3+ Kh6 23. g4 $1 {[%cal Ge3h3]} (23. Rd4 g5 24. h4 $18)) 22. Qc3 {[%cal Gc3h8]}) 21. Rd5 Qe8 22. Qc3 f6 23. Nxd8 Bxd5 24. cxd5 Qxd8 25. Be6+ Kg7 26. b4 Nb7 27. Qc6 a5 28. a3 axb4 29. axb4 Kf8 30. Rd3 Qe8 31. Bd7 Qd8 32. h4 Kg7 33. Kh2 Qf8 34. Qxb6 Nc5 35. bxc5 Rxb6 36. cxb6 Qd8 37. Rb3 Qxd7 38. b7 Qf5 39. Kg1 Qc2 40. b8=Q Qd1+ 41. Kh2 Qxe2 42. Qb6 h5 43. Qe3 Qd1 44. Qxe7+ Kh6 45. Qf8+ Kh7 46. Rb7# 1-0

