1. c4 c5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. g3 g6 4. b3 Bg7 5. Bb2 b6 6. Bg2 Bb7 7. O-O O-O 8. Nc3 d5 (8... d6 9. d4 cxd4 10. Qxd4 {We can take with the queen, but taking with the knight also leads to a playable position} (10. Nxd4 Bxg2 11. Kxg2 Qc7 12. e4 $14)) 9. Nxd5 $1 {Not cxd5 as we would be pinned on the diagonal} Nxd5 10. Bxg7 Kxg7 11. cxd5 Qxd5 12. d4 cxd4 (12... Nd7 $4 {Black needs to be careful, this loses a piece} 13. Ne1 {[%csl Rb7][%cal Gg2b7]}) 13. Qxd4+ Qxd4 14. Nxd4 Bxg2 15. Kxg2 {This is a playable endgame where White can press a bit. With best play, Black will make a draw but if you like to play endgames, this one gives pretty good chances for White} Rc8 16. Rac1 Nd7 17. Rfd1 Nc5 18. b4 Na4 19. Nb5 Rxc1 20. Rxc1 a5 21. a3 Rd8 22. Rc7 {[%csl Ra4] The knight on a4 is a bit misplaced and White has the better-placed pieces} Rd5 23. Na7 axb4 24. axb4 e6 25. Nc6 Rd2 26. Ne5 Rxe2 27. Nxf7 h5 28. Ng5+ Kf6 29. Kf1 Rxf2+ 30. Kxf2 Kxg5 31. Ke3 Kg4 32. b5 Kh3 33. Rc4 Nb2 34. Rc2 1-0

