1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. b3 Bg7 4. Bb2 O-O 5. g3 c5 6. Bg2 d6 (6... Nc6 7. O-O d5 $6 {You will see this mistake quite often. Black tries to be active but ends up in a worse and passive position.} (7... d6 8. d4 $14) 8. cxd5 Nxd5 9. Bxg7 Kxg7 10. d4 cxd4 11. Nxd4 Nxd4 (11... Ndb4 12. Nxc6 $1 Nxc6 13. Bxc6 $1 bxc6 $14 {[%csl Rc6]} 14. Qxd8 Rxd8 15. Nc3 Be6 16. Rfd1 f6 17. f3 Kf7 18. Kf2 $16 c5 19. Rac1 c4 20. b4 $3 $16 Rdb8 (20... Ke8 21. Rxd8+ (21. Ke3 $16) 21... Rxd8 22. Rd1 Rxd1 23. Nxd1 Kd8 24. Ke3 Kc7 25. Nc3 Kd6 26. Kd4 $16) 21. a3 $1 a5 22. b5 $16) 12. Qxd4+ Nf6 13. Qe5 Qd6 14. Qxd6 exd6 15. Nc3 $16) 7. d4 $1 {Since there are many transpositions and move orders, remember the rule: - We can only play d4 after Bg2!! Never before Bg2.} (7. O-O $5 {Allowing the Reti KID with d6-e5-c5 is also good. It's more for players who prefer slow maneuvering games} e5 8. d3 Nc6 9. Nc3 $14) 7... cxd4 (7... Nc6 8. O-O Ne4 9. Nbd2 Nxd2 10. Qxd2 cxd4 11. Nxd4 Nxd4 12. Bxd4 Bxd4 13. Qxd4 $14) 8. Nxd4 d5 9. cxd5 Nxd5 10. O-O a6 (10... Nc6 $6 11. Nxc6 bxc6 {[%csl Rc6]} 12. Bxg7 Kxg7 13. Qd4+ Kg8 14. Nc3 $16) 11. Qd2 $1 Nb6 12. Rd1 e5 13. Nf5 $3 Qxd2 14. Ne7+ Kh8 15. Rxd2 Be6 16. Nc3 Re8 17. Ned5 Nxd5 18. Nxd5 Rd8 19. Rad1 Nc6 20. Nc7 Rxd2 21. Rxd2 Rd8 22. Rxd8+ Nxd8 23. Nxe6 fxe6 1-0

