1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 g6 3. b3 Bg7 4. Bb2 O-O 5. Bg2 d6 6. c4 e5 (6... c5 7. O-O (7. d4 {Objectively the best move is d4, but if you have learned how to play the positions with d3, you can allow Black to play the c5-d6-e5 set-up}) 7... e5 8. d3) 7. d3 Nh5 {Be careful of this move, whenever the bishops are starting at each other, there may be potential tactics with e4 from Black - the protected bishop usually wins in such tactics (which is the Bg7 at the moment)} 8. Nc3 $1 {Closing the diagonal} Nc6 9. O-O f5 10. e3 (10. Nd2 $1 f4 {[%cal Gc8g4] Threatening Bg4} (10... Bd7 11. Nd5 $14) (10... g5 11. e3 {[%cal Gd1h5]} Nf6 12. Nd5 Ne7 13. Nxf6+ {I would like to eliminate the more active knight on f6} Bxf6 14. b4 (14. f4 {directly is also good}) 14... Ng6 15. b5 {We continue our play with natural moves, and we wait for Black to create weaknesses trying to attack us} f4 $6 16. Ne4 $16) 11. e3 $1 {Preventing Bg4} (11. Nd5 $6 Bg4 $3 12. Ne4 Nd4 $3 13. Bxd4 exd4 $15) 11... Bh6 12. Qe2 $14 (12. Nd5 {is also possible})) 10... g5 (10... f4 $6 11. Nd2 $1 $14 fxe3 12. fxe3 Bh6 13. Rxf8+ $1 Qxf8 14. Nd5 Qd8 15. Qe2 Be6 16. Rf1 $16) 11. Nd2 (11. Nxe5 $2 Nxe5 12. Qxh5 Nxd3 $17) 11... Nf6 (11... g4 12. f3 $3 $14) 12. Nd5 $1 Nxd5 13. cxd5 Ne7 14. Rc1 $1 $14 (14. e4 $6 f4 $132) 14... Ng6 15. Rc4 $3 Rf7 (15... Bd7 16. Qc2 Rc8 17. Rc1 $18) 16. a4 $3 (16. Qc2 b5 17. Rc6 Bb7) 16... a5 17. Qc2 b6 18. Rc1 Ra7 19. Rc6 $3 Ba6 (19... f4 20. Ne4 $1 (20. Be4 {is an idea to get the bishop out before any potential f3 later forces it to go to f1}) 20... f3 $2 21. Nxd6 $18 (21. Bf1 $14)) 20. e4 $16 Qd7 (20... Ne7 21. Rxc7 $18) (20... f4 $2 21. Bh3 $1 Bc8 22. Bxc8 Qxc8 23. Rxd6 $16) 21. exf5 Qxf5 22. Nc4 Qf6 23. Ne3 Bxd3 24. Qd2 Bf5 (24... Ba6 25. Be4 $16) 25. Nxf5 Qxf5 26. Qe2 Qd7 (26... e4 27. Bxe4 $18) 27. Qh5 Qf5 28. Qe2 Qd7 29. Qc2 Nf8 30. Be4 Kh8 31. Bc3 $3 {Transferring the bishop to e3!} Qd8 32. Bd2 $1 Qf6 33. Be3 h6 34. Qe2 $1 Kg8 35. R1c4 Qd8 36. Qc2 Rb7 37. Bf5 Bf6 38. b4 axb4 39. Rxb4 Qa8 40. Kg2 Kg7 41. h4 Ra7 42. hxg5 Bxg5 43. Rg4 Ra5 44. Bxg5 hxg5 45. Rxg5+ Kf6 46. Rh5 Rxd5 47. Be4 Qa5 48. Rf5+ Kg7 49. Rxc7 Rd7 50. Qc6 1-0

