1. Nf3 f5 2. d3 d6 3. e4 g6 $2 (3... e5 {The best try for Black.} 4. Nc3 c5 5. g3 $1 Nc6 6. Bh3 $1 $14 {This is all you need to remember. Against 2...d6 you go e4 and on e5 you play Nc3! with g3 and then Bh3 or Nh4. Against all other variations from the Dutch, White is much better.}) 4. exf5 Bxf5 5. d4 $16 Bg7 6. Bd3 (6. Bc4 {is also a good move (White is potentially provoking d5 which would weaken the e5 square and Black's e pawn even further).}) 6... Qd7 7. O-O Nf6 8. Re1 Nc6 9. c3 O-O-O 10. Bb5 $5 e5 $2 11. d5 $18 Nxd5 12. Qxd5 Be6 13. Qd1 a6 14. Ba4 Rdf8 15. Be3 d5 16. Bc5 Rf5 17. Nbd2 b6 18. Ba3 b5 19. Bc2 e4 20. Nxe4 dxe4 21. Bxe4 Rf4 22. Ng5 Bg4 23. f3 Bf5 24. Qc1 Rh4 25. Qe3 b4 26. Rad1 Bd4 27. cxd4 bxa3 28. Qxa3 Bxe4 29. Qxa6+ Kb8 30. Rxe4 Rxe4 31. Nxe4 Nxd4 32. Rd3 Re8 33. Qc4 Rd8 34. Nc5 Qd5 35. Qxd5 Rxd5 36. b4 Ne2+ 37. Kf2 Rxd3 38. Nxd3 Nc3 39. a3 Kc8 40. g4 Kd7 41. h4 Ke6 42. Ke3 Kd5 43. f4 Nd1+ 44. Kd2 Kd4 45. Kxd1 Kxd3 46. f5 gxf5 47. gxf5 Kc4 48. f6 Kb3 49. f7 Kxa3 50. f8=Q c5 51. Qxc5 h5 52. Qxh5 Ka4 53. Qg5 Kb3 54. h5 Ka4 55. h6 Kb3 56. h7 Kc4 57. h8=Q Kb3 58. b5 Ka4 59. b6 Kb3 60. Qf4 Ka2 61. Qa8+ Kb3 62. Qaa4+ Kc3 63. Qfd4# 1-0

