1. Nf3 f5 2. d3 g6 3. e4 d6 4. h4 $5 $16 {A very interesting plan! Black is only playing with the pawns and not developing, so the idea of h4-h5 is very threatening since Black played g6.} (4. exf5 {This is the simplest - the usual plan exf5 Bxf5 and d4!} Bxf5 5. d4 $16) 4... Bg7 (4... Nf6 5. h5 Nxh5 6. Rxh5 $1 {A good rook sacrifice to break down Black's structure and open up Black's king position.} gxh5 7. Ng5 $16) 5. h5 Nh6 6. Nc3 {At some moment White will find a way to move the d pawn to d4 and claim a bigger advantage, Nc3 protects the e4 pawn to make d4 possible.} c6 7. d4 Nf7 8. Bc4 e6 9. hxg6 hxg6 10. Rxh8+ Bxh8 11. Qe2 fxe4 12. Qxe4 d5 13. Qxg6 dxc4 14. Bg5 Qd6 15. Ne4 Qf8 16. Ne5 $18 Bxe5 17. dxe5 Kd7 18. O-O-O+ Kc7 19. Qxf7+ Nd7 20. Qxf8 Nxf8 21. Bd8+ Kb8 22. Be7 1-0

