1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 a6 4. b3 c5 5. Bg2 b5 6. Nc3 Qb6 7. O-O Bb7 8. Bb2 (8. Re1 $1 Be7 9. e4 O-O 10. e5 $14) 8... Be7 (8... bxc4 $6 9. bxc4 Qxb2 $2 10. Rb1 $18 {[%csl Gb7][%cal Gb1b7]}) 9. d4 $5 {This leads by force to an almost equal endgame where the great Ulf Andersson managed to outplay his opponent, it is an interesting line indeed!} cxd4 10. Qxd4 Qxd4 11. Nxd4 Bxg2 12. Kxg2 bxc4 13. bxc4 d6 14. Na4 Nbd7 15. Rfd1 Rc8 16. Rac1 O-O {The c4 pawn is weak but d6 is also weak. White has a better bishop and White's king is more active.} 17. Nb3 $14 {With a small and steady advantage which Ulf Andersson likes.} Ne4 {With Ne4, Black wants to exchange all the knights through the c5 square.} (17... Nc5 $6 18. Naxc5 $1 {Nbxc5 was also possible but keeping the b3 knight is better.} dxc5 19. Bxf6 $5 {With this, White enters a good knight against a bad bishop position.} gxf6 (19... Bxf6 {The bishop at first sight is good but it can't coordinate with any other Black piece and c5 is permanently weak.} 20. Rd6 $16 {White starts to target Black's weaknesses.}) 20. Rd7 Rfe8 21. g4 $16 {After g4, any pawn push such as f5, h5, or e5 won't be good. White also has a way for the king towards the center. White has a big advantage and practically it might be winning for White.}) 18. Bd4 {[%csl Rc5][%cal Gd4c5]} (18. f3 $6 {This is not good because it allows Black's idea.} Nec5 19. Naxc5 Nxc5 20. Nxc5 Rxc5 {The bishops are more or less equal and both sides have a pawn weakness - on c4 and d6.} 21. Ba3 Rc6 $11) 18... Rfd8 (18... Ndc5 19. Bxc5 Nxc5 20. Naxc5 dxc5 21. Rd7 $16 {We already saw a different version of this position. Black's bishop is a really bad piece with no prospects. The knight on b3 is good and puts pressure on c5.}) 19. f3 Nec5 20. Naxc5 Nxc5 21. Nxc5 (21. Bxc5 $1 {White should have taken with the bishop and create the minor piece imbalance good knight versus bad bishop.} dxc5 22. f4 $14) 21... dxc5 22. Be3 {Leaving the bishop instead of the knight is also possible since White is also better here.} Rxd1 23. Rxd1 Rb8 24. Rd7 Bf8 25. Ra7 Rb4 26. Rxa6 Rxc4 27. Kf2 e5 28. g4 f6 29. Ra7 h5 30. gxh5 f5 31. Bg5 e4 32. Bf4 exf3 33. Kxf3 Rc3+ 34. e3 c4 35. Be5 Rc2 36. a4 Ra2 37. a5 Kh7 38. a6 Ra5 39. Bc3 Ra3 40. Bd4 c3 41. Ra8 c2 42. Bb2 Ra2 43. Rxf8 Rxb2 44. Rc8 Ra2 45. Kf4 Rxa6 46. Rxc2 Re6 47. Re2 Rh6 48. Kg5 Rf6 49. h3 Rf7 50. Rf2 Re7 51. Rf3 Re5 52. Kf4 Ra5 53. Rg3 Rb5 54. Rg5 Rb4+ 55. Kxf5 Rh4 56. e4 Rxh3 57. e5 Kg8 58. Ke6 Kf8 59. Rf5+ Kg8 60. Rg5 Kf8 61. Rf5+ Ke8 62. Rf7 Rxh5 63. Re7+ Kf8 64. Kd7 g6 65. Kd8 Rh1 66. e6 Re1 67. Rf7+ Kg8 68. Ke7 Re2 69. Kd7 Ra2 70. Rf1 Ra7+ 71. Ke8 Ra8+ 72. Ke7 Ra2 73. Rd1 Kg7 74. Ke8 Ra8+ 75. Rd8 1-0

