1. c4 e6 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. g3 a6 4. Bg2 b5 5. b3 Bb7 6. Nc3 b4 7. Na4 c5 8. O-O d6 9. d4 cxd4 (9... Nbd7 10. Bg5 {White could have also taken dxc5 immediately.} Be7 11. dxc5 Nxc5 12. Nxc5 dxc5 13. Qxd8+ Rxd8 14. Rfd1 O-O 15. Ne5 (15. Ne1 {This move is also good.} Bxg2 16. Kxg2 h6 17. Bxf6 Bxf6 18. Rab1 Bc3 19. Nd3 $14 {White is better and will soon take over.}) 15... Bxg2 16. Kxg2 h6 17. Be3 $16) 10. Nxd4 Bxg2 11. Kxg2 Qc7 12. Qd3 {Generally in the Romanishin variation White wants to exchange the queens and Black should keep them on the board.} Nbd7 13. f4 {A typical move to put the queen on f3 and control the e5 square, so there is no Ne5 to harass the queen.} Be7 14. Qf3 Rc8 15. Bd2 $14 Nc5 16. Nb2 Qb6 17. Be3 O-O 18. g4 Nfe4 19. Nd3 Bf6 20. Nxc5 dxc5 21. Qxe4 Bxd4 22. Bxd4 cxd4 23. Rad1 Rcd8 24. h3 Rfe8 25. Rf3 Qc5 26. Qe5 Qb6 27. g5 Rf8 28. Qe4 f6 29. gxf6 Rxf6 30. Rfd3 Rdf8 31. Rxd4 Rxf4 32. Qxf4 Rxf4 33. Rxf4 h6 34. Rf3 Qa5 35. Rd7 Qxa2 36. Kf2 a5 37. Rff7 Qxb3 38. Rxg7+ Kf8 39. Rdf7+ Ke8 40. Rb7 Kf8 41. Rgc7 1-0

