{[%evp 0,75,20,20,14,-1,5,-23,25,19,19,2,26,31,32,37,37,-2,38,22,38,59,62,35,51,7,0,25,30,38,59,56,53,94,114,117,182,164,164,164,173,153,146,118,119,119,114,90,121,126,108,130,127,107,125,128,119,125,119,133,119,119,117,122,147,129,124,135,183,176,189,187,200,164,157,170,275,379]} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 a6 4. Bg2 b5 5. b3 c5 6. Nc3 Qb6 7. O-O Bb7 8. Re1 Be7 9. e4 d6 $2 {This is almost losing by force. The correct idea is only 9... 0-0} 10. d4 $1 $16 {The center opens up and Black is behind in development.} cxd4 11. Nxd4 b4 (11... bxc4 12. bxc4 Qc7 (12... Nbd7 13. Rb1 Qc7 14. Rxb7 Qxb7 15. e5 $18) 13. Rb1 Bc6 14. Nd5 $18 (14. e5 $18)) 12. Nd5 $3 exd5 13. exd5 Bc8 {This move prevents Nf5.} 14. Bg5 {Threatening to take on f6 and play a slow positional game.} h6 (14... Nbd7 $2 15. Nc6 $18) 15. Bxf6 gxf6 16. c5 $1 dxc5 (16... Qd8 $2 17. c6 $18 {White has tremendous positional compensation for the piece and is completely dominating all the Black pieces!} a5 18. Qh5 Na6 19. Bh3 Bxh3 20. Qxh3 {[%csl Gf5][%cal Gd4f5] A knight is coming to f5 next and it will be time for Black to resign.}) 17. d6 Qxd6 18. Nc6 Qxd1 19. Raxd1 {[%csl Gd8][%cal Gd1d8]} Be6 20. Nxe7 Ra7 21. Ng6 Rg8 22. Nf4 Re7 23. Bd5 Bxd5 24. Nxd5 Rxe1+ 25. Rxe1+ Kd8 26. Nxf6 Rg6 27. Re8+ Kc7 28. Re7+ Kd6 29. Rxf7 Ke6 30. Rb7 Rxf6 31. Rxb8 Ke5 32. f4+ Kd4 33. Kf2 a5 34. Ra8 c4 35. bxc4 Rf5 36. Kf3 Kxc4 37. Ke4 Rc5 38. f5 1-0

