1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 a6 4. Bg2 b5 5. b3 Bb7 6. Nc3 Bb4 $5 {This is possibly the best move for Black. White is slightly better after either Bb2 or Qc2.} 7. Bb2 (7. cxb5 Bxc3 {This is Black's idea, after cxb5 to play Bxc3 intermediate move.} 8. dxc3 axb5 9. Qd3 {Now even} Ra5 {is acceptable for Black. We can play a simpler game with 7.Bb2} (9... Bc6 {This is another move that Black can play instead of Ra5.})) 7... O-O 8. Qc2 {White is setting up a trap with this move. Black should take bxc4 in this Bb4 variation and at the end, White is just slightly better.} d6 $2 (8... bxc4 9. bxc4 d6 10. Rb1 c5 11. O-O $14) 9. cxb5 Bxc3 10. Bxc3 Nbd7 {Black needs to play this move in order after Ng5 to take Bxg2 and not be mated.} (10... axb5 $4 11. Ng5 $1 $18 {[%csl Gh7][%cal Gc3f6,Gc2h7,Gg2b7]} Bxg2 12. Bxf6 {And Black is lost.}) 11. bxa6 Rxa6 12. O-O Qa8 13. d3 $16 {Black has little compensation for the missing pawn but it's not much.} e5 14. a4 c5 15. e4 Ng4 16. Nh4 f5 17. Bh3 h5 18. Nxf5 Rxf5 19. exf5 Ndf6 20. Rfe1 Qc8 21. Bg2 Bxg2 22. Kxg2 Nd5 23. Bd2 Qxf5 24. f3 Ngf6 25. Qc4 Ra7 26. a5 Rf7 27. Rf1 h4 28. g4 Qd7 29. g5 Nf4+ 30. Bxf4 d5 31. Qxc5 Ng4 32. fxg4 Qxg4+ 33. Kh1 Rxf4 34. Qxd5+ 1-0

